    <h1>How to Stop Muscle Loss After 50<br><span class="green">(It's Not Inevitable)</span></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">Most men assume muscle loss is just what happens with age. It isn't. It's a response to two things — and both of them are fixable. Here's the exact playbook.</p>
    <p style="color:#6ee7a0;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;margin-top:1rem;">Most men aren't low on effort — they're low on protein.</p>
    <p class="hero-meta">SnapProtein &nbsp;·&nbsp; 8 min read</p>
  </header>

