        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q">Can you stop muscle loss after 50?</div>
          <div class="faq-a">Yes. Muscle loss after 50 is not inevitable — it is largely driven by two controllable factors: insufficient protein intake and insufficient resistance training. Research consistently shows that men over 50 who address both can halt sarcopenia progression and in many cases build meaningful muscle.</div>
